`prompts/` holds the two prompt templates that drive the context-summarization pipeline: one instructs an LLM to generate a leaf `.ctx` from a source file, the other instructs it to generate a directory `rollup.ctx` from child `.ctx`/`rollup.ctx` files. Depending on this directory means depending on the wording an LLM sees at generation time — there is no executable code here, so "editing" these files directly changes pipeline output quality and format, not behavior via logic.

The two prompts must stay vocabulary-consistent — both use "context document," describe themselves as replacing an existing `.ctx`/`rollup.ctx`, and both enumerate a banned-phrase list and an anti-duplication rule. If one prompt's framing, tone, or structural rules (prose-only, no fixed schema, line-budget deference to `docs/SPEC.md`) changes, the other should be checked for drift. Each embeds a worked example that is calibration for length/register/density as much as illustration, so an edit to the surrounding rules should keep the example internally consistent with them.

The two files are peers with no shared code, only shared contract: summarizer-leaf.md.ctx governs the base case (file → `.ctx`), summarizer-rollup.md.ctx governs the recursive case (children's `.ctx`/`rollup.ctx` → `rollup.ctx`). A typical edit to this subtree starts from a complaint about generated output (too verbose, duplicating child content, missing an invariant) and traces to a rule or example in the relevant prompt.

intent.md is empty, so no divergence can be assessed against it.